"7CF54660361E11EBAB23F9C93F01EB9A","previous_id":1087605,"previous_guid":"01165D50361811EBAB23F9C93F01EB9A","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"B943B365F7334185AA6BF92495F695D6","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Isolation for RNA extraction"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"4C252C1AEDA4403B8A82B2B81E3456E1","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Prepare small plastic zip-locked bags for the samples along with a sample label (pencil on water-proof paper).<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":1800,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1087621,"guid":"11093990362111EBAB23F9C93F01EB9A","previous_id":1087574,"previous_guid":"9ED9ECE0361411EBAB23F9C93F01EB9A","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"582561865AEE4072A51600B9B43C2FA3","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA extraction"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"03F24225166D4375ADA96D08FBA45931","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Follow the protocol for RNA extraction.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Single-cell total RNA extraction from marine protists (e.g. Acantharia, <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Strombidium <\/span><span>cf <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">basimorphum<\/span><span>, and <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Prymnesium parvum<\/span><span>).<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/private\/EDB0E27A323211EB952C0A58A9FEAC2A\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/private\/EDB0E27A323211EB952C0A58A9FEAC2A<\/span><\/a><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":"","materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:left\">Many marine protists are not culturable and therefore challenging to study, nonetheless, they are essential in all marine ecosystems. The development of single-cell techniques is allowing for more marine protists to be studied. Thereby Cultivation-independent studies are essential for the study of organisms sensitive to the sampling procedure, such as Radiolaria.<\/div><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:left\"><\/div><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:left\"><span>This method describes the means to acquire clean isolated single-cells from plankton nets for physiological and\/or transcriptomic analysis. The isolation of cells in this protocol is followed by preparing the cells for RNA extraction (protocol: Single-cell total RNA extraction from marine protists (e.g. Acantharia, <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Strombidium <\/span><span>cf <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">basimorphum<\/span><span>, and <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Prymnesium parvum<\/span><span>)).<\/span><\/div><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:left\"><\/div><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:left\"><\/div><\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1610446876}